text: Did you know seaweed is a zero-input food source? Unlike crops that are grown on land, seaweed requires no additional fresh water, fertilizer, pesticides, feed, or soil to grow. text: Frickin’ Fried Chicken!⭐️Wing Wing🍴6 wings, 6 drumsticks, regular chips and seaweed chips🍗When you need a pick me up on a Monday! My colleague and I had planned to go for KFC since end of last year. Finally made it on Monday, we were so excited to we took an early lunch and headed to Bloomsbury. We didn’t know what to go for so ordered the lot! We definitely overordered but it was so good that we ate most of it spare some chips and I took a wing away in a doggy bag. We went for mix flavours, hot, liquorice and soy ginger. Generally I am not a fan of liquorice at all, but I heard it was great on the kfc so thought why not. It doesn’t taste much liquorice at all! In fact very similar to the soy ginger but a bit sweeter. Definitely recommend trying the mix! And seaweed chips! Gives the chips extra seasoning. Normally I prefer wings but these drumsticks were soo juicy and tender and had a lot more meat, so next time I’d just get 3 drumsticks and chips. Just drooling from the memory. If you go, the peak time is 1pm so definitely avoid then. text: Toasted Seaweed ChipsMaking your own nori chips is easy and much cheaper than buying the prepackaged versions.I picked up one the other day and saw on the ingredient list ‘vegetable oil’. This has a negative effect on the body. Just make your own and save yourself the $. Ingredients:nori sheetsolive oilsea saltoptionals: sesame seeds, onion powder, garlic powder, nutritional yeast.Method:Preheat over to 160 C.Mix the oil and your optional toppings.Cut the nori sheets into equal sizes and brush the shiny side with the oil mix.Place on a baking tray lined with paper.Bake for 10 - 15 minutes or until crisp.Facts about seaweed:Seaweed is high in iodine which is a key component of the hormones made in the thyroid gland. Thyroid hormones regulate the body’s metabolism, promote healthy heart function, muscle control, mood and bone maintenance. If you have a thyroid condition, please consult with your health practitioner to know if seaweed is good for you.

text: When you have stale nori and leftover spring roll wrappers...make some nori crunchy rolls!Ingredients:Nori sheetsVegan Spring roll wrappers3 tbs flour (use any flour you like)Salt, pepper and garlic powder to tasteWaterHerbs or any flavoring you like (optional)Direction:1.Thaw the wrappers.2. Mix flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and water. You want to have a thin consistency, which is slightly runnier than than pancake batter.3. Once thawed, take the spring roll wrapper and spread the thin paste on to the wrappers. You can use brush but i prefer doing it with my hands 😉.4. Lay the nori sheet, rough side down, on top of the wrapper. For those who love extra crunchiness...repeat step 3 and sandwhiched the nori in between the wrappers.5. Dry the sheets for at least and hour. Use knife or scissors to cut the sheets to your liking.6. In medium high heat, deep fry the sheets. Keep an eye on it because they get browned up very quickly.7. Enjoy! Or...add extra flavoring like herbs, bbq powder, cheese, powdered salt and sugar...options are endless...but i like mine just as is!#govegan #hclfplantbased #vegan #whatveganseat #veganfoodshare #plantbaseddiet #plantbasedfoodrocks  #instavegan #instaplantbased #instafood #instafoodie #vegansofig #foodphotography #pepzkitchen #foodgasm #foodporn #foodgram #seaweedchips #norichips #kerupukrumputlaut #seaweedcrackers #makanenak #veganindonesia #vegansurabaya #sumpia #sumpiarumputlaut #veganrecipeshare #veganrecipes

text: 🔥 🏈 🔥 Looking for last minute plant-based Sunday Funday, Big Game Day eats? 🔥 🏈 🔥We love eating Chomperz right outta the bag, but that BIG BOLD FLAVOR adds the ultimate #umami crunch 💥 to your favorite dips too! This bean free hummus is a simple but smoky, savory, thick and creamy alternative to #hummus that’s rich in fiber and real ingredients. Smoky Roasted Cauliflower & Garlic Dip 🔥 🏈 🔥 No beans.💯 #keto #plantbased and easy to make. 1.5 cups roasted cauliflower (2.5 cups dry)2-4 garlic 🧄 cloves, roasted*3-4 tbsp olive oil***Or (2 tbsp @majesticgarlic creamy original garlic spread + 2 tbsp olive oil)1/2 tsp smoked paprika 1 tbsp @coconutsecretofficial Sea salt to taste Served up with a side of #seasnax Barbecue Chomperz for maximum crunch. 😋 Method:Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Lay out cauliflower florets on a non-stick baking sheet with garlic cloves, if using. (Use more if you’re a fan of garlic 😉). Sprinkle lightly with sea salt. Bake for 30 minutes, or until florets are cooked through and browning at the edges. Carefully scoop into a small blender or food processor with oil or Majestic Garlic + oil. Blend until well combined then add paprika. Blend again and season with sea salt to taste. Serve at room temperature or warmed. 🔥 📸: @glow_detox

Kelp forests can sequester up to 20 times more carbon per acre than land forests. This can help reverse acidification as well as the negative effects that a lower pH level has on marine life.⁠⁠💚💚💚 It's SOO good for you. text: Salty and crunchy. I took dulse seaweed and placed it in a cast iron skillet stove top for about three minutes on low heat, turned off the heat, and let the leaves cool to a crisp! No added salt or seasoning needed! 20+ years ago when I used to make these for my son, I would bake them in the oven, but I often burned them because they need very little heat to remove the moisture and turn into a crisp chip! Soooo crunchy! Wish I had some guacamole!#dulsechips#seaweedchips

text: Seaweed or sea vegetables are forms of algae that grow in the sea.They’re a food source for ocean life and range in color from red to green to brown to black.Seaweed grows along rocky shorelines around the world, but it’s most commonly eaten in Asian countries such as Japan, Korea and China.It’s extremely versatile and can be used in many dishes, including sushi rolls, soups and stews, salads, supplements and smoothies. There are numerous benefits  of eating  sea weed, like * it contains Iodine and Tyrosine, which supports  Thyroid Function * it is a good source of Vitamins and Minerals * it contains a variety  of Antioxidants * it is rich in gut friendly fibresAnd so much more. text: Winkles for tea! Have you spotted the mistake? These aren't winkles, they're mostly top shells, which are also edible. ..As the crescent moon fattens up again, and we leave the big tides behind, winkles, perwinkles, topshells and whelks are still easy to find at the top of the shore. Often in clusters, topshells have a toothed pattern (see 3rd image) and mother of pearl inside, while winkles (last image) are dark and plain. ..Winkles, also known as common perwinkle (Littorina littorea) - who knows latin, does that mean littered, i.e commonly scattered around? ..Eaten for thousands of years, they're a sustainable alternative to large scale fishing by trawlers. Fitting perfectly into slow food, you eat the flesh by knocking off the outer disc then using a pin to fish (excuse the pun) the winkle out. ..Did you know that winkles and top shells are both vegetarian? Eating a diet of seaweeds, these univalves are a lot safer to eat than mussels and other bivalves. They're an easy treat to pluck. I'll be posting a blog in a couple of days to give you more information, including a dead easy recipe. Have a good weekend.

text: The slimy & slippery seaweed is recognised as the new superfood. Seaweeds are full of nutrients & are rich in minerals, most prominently in calcium, copper, iodine and iron. .This popular sea plant is also loaded with protein, fibre and vitamins, specifically vitamin K and folic acid. They are low in calories & in fat..With all these beneficial nutritional profile, seaweed is considered as the best & must have food. .Popular varieties of seaweed include:➡️ Nori➡️ Kelp➡️ Wakame➡️ Kombu➡️ Dulse➡️ Blue-green algae.Proven Health Benefits of seaweed:✔️ May help with diabetes - seaweed is rich in fiber & high amount of fiber regulates glucose & insulin levels.✔️ May aid in Thyroid reduction - Kombu is the richest source of Iodine that can improve hypothyroidism✔️ May support gut health - algae is fiber rich that feeds gut bacteria✔️ May help with weight loss - seaweed is rich in dietary fiber, it helps delaying stomach emptying..Any Side Effects? 🔹 Over consumption of seaweed results in consuming too much iodine. While some can handle this, but others are vulnerable to the effects which may result in thyroid dysfunction. 🔹 Edible seaweeds have lower levels of dangerous metals like aluminium & cadmium. However, when over consumed, these metals may build up overtime. text: "Tuna" sandwich ! 😲 Yes indeedy!And it tastes like the real thing! 👌🏾 *see previous post for the full sandwich* This recipe serves 4.Ingredients: ciabatta bread,  2/3 of a can of green or young jackfruit, 1/2 can of chickpeas, 3 sticks of celery, 1/4 of a white onion, 3 tablespoons of hummus, fresh cracked black pepper, a pinch of salt, a splash of apple cider vinegar, and 1/2 a package of roasted seaweed snacks/chips. Recipe:Thoroughly rinse the jackfruit at least three times. Cut off the tough part on one end. Shred the Jackfruit and remove the seeds with your hands. Thoroughly rinse the chickpeas at least three times, then smash them on a cutting board; they should still be recognizable. Combine the two ingredients together. Form the mixture into medium-to-large sized balls, then squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Put it in the refrigerator until you're ready to use it.Dice your celery and onions into very small pieces. Shred up your seaweed snacks. Add these ingredients to a bowl with the Jackfruit and smashed chickpeas. Add your hummus, black pepper, salt, and apple cider vinegar. Stir the ingredients until everything is evenly distributed. Taste the mixture to make sure it is well seasoned. You can use vegan mayonnaise instead of hummus. You can substitute the apple cider vinegar for lemon juice.Toast your bread on both sides with your choice of oil in a non-stick pan or cast iron skillet. Spread your tuna salad on to the bread, then eat! This recipe took about 20 to 30 minutes for me to prepare. Ideally it should have been done when I wasn't starving LOL. It definitely hit the spot! The bonus for me was the fact that I still got in my carbs, protein, and fiber. I hope you try it out 😀. #jackfruit#chickpeas #ciabatta /#ciabattabread#celery #onions #blackpepper#salt#hummus#applecidervinegar #seaweedsnacks / #seaweedchips#vegantuna#vegan

text: We met Ulla de Frey on the island of Ærœ. Ærœ is a self-sufficient island in Denmark that produces its energy 120% with renewables. Ulla had gathered this seaweed kelp from the Baltic Sea, fried them in the oven with a hint of oil. These climate-friendly chips have a delicious story to tell about the waters they swim in. Blatter wrack seaweed creates a habitat for dozens of species and there is no other species that could replace the importance of kelp in the ecosystem of the Baltic Sea. This seaweed contains huge amount of minerals and vitamins, naturally high concentrations of iodine and potassium. It is nutritious food for us humans as well and can be used either dried, boiled or steamed. It serves also as a good fertilizer and soil improvement for crops.Climate-friendly food has almost as big effect on the environment as ecological housing and transport options. Diet can be changed pro-climate with small steps: Walk or bicycle to the grocery store, favor local vegetables, mushrooms and berries that are produced near or gathered wild. Dry, ferment and preserve. Pack the shopping in a basket or tote bag. And no need to be absolute here. Start by being aware and then begin to replace some of the not-so-good choices with climate-friendly alternatives. Climate-friendly food is usually cheap or better yet free, at least in Finland. But be sure to leave some blatter wreck for the fish and seafood!Read more about climate-friendly food from the next #latujapolku magazine. Also a photo reportage about our Meri-Pori adventures will be published there next Friday.More info about using kelp as cosmetics coming soon.Photo: @ainohuotari#blatterwreck #klimaatti #climatediet #ipreferbetterthings #chips #seaweedchips #seaweed #wildfood #ipreferbetterthings #oceanismyboyfriend #act4climate #bseuroroaming #fairtrippin #fairtravelling #renewableenergy #ecochef

text: Seaweed chips or is that Nori Chips 🤔 either way...I popped the oven on 180deg l, spread a thin layer of sesame oil over each side of four full sheets and one halved sheet (you just fold them and they break) then sprinkled with some fine rosemary salt on one side only (as that’s what I had on hand), be sure not to be too heavy on the salt lol, then I popped two on the top tray down the back and the halved ones in front of them and then two down the bottom -Be careful not to burn yourself obv... 😘 making sure they don’t touch...5mins later BOOM 💥 We have seaweed/nori chips...I folded each square in half, each half in half & those halves in halves until you have manageable pieces.They keep drying out until their cold I think (they’re never hot to the touch).#enjoy #homemade #norichips #seaweedchips #easy #youchoose #kidslove #cheapaschips #mintfitnesspt @mintfitnesspt

text: Hai! Cobain snack baru yang kekinian nih, Japota. Snack potato chips terbaru dari Calbee Wings yang terbuat dari kentang asli, diolah menggunakan thin-cut technology sehingga memiliki tekstur yang #AsliKrenyesnya. Tersedia dalam 2 pilihan rasa, Umami Japanese Seaweed dan Happy Honey Butter yang bikin kamu gak bisa nolak enaknya..Kamis, 11 Juli 2019 kemarin, Japota mengadakan Press Conference peluncuran produknya secara resmi di Kantorkuu - Coworking space, Agro Plaza Kuningan. Dihadiri oleh banyak awak media cetak, digital dan juga TV, press conference mengangkat tema "Millennials snacking habits" yang dikorelasikan dengan mengenalkan Japota sebagai pilihan snack baru untuk millennials. Dipandu oleh MC @mpatrick , event peluncuran Japota turut mengundang narasumber yang tak kalah serunya, ada @mbrian87 (Senior Brand Manager Japota), @veraitabhadiwidjojo (Psikolog) dan @patriciagouw (Model & Influencer)..Dalam press conference ini banyak dibahas bagaimana habit millennials ditengah kesibukan dan gaya hidupnya sangat tidak dapat dipisahakan dari kebiasaan snacking. Maka dari itu, Japota hadir sebagai pilihan snack potato chips baru dengan menawarkan tekstur yang #AsliKrenyesnya dan keunikan rasa yang gak bisa ditolak enaknya..Japota diharapkan dapat diterima dan disukai oleh masyarakat Indonesia sebagai snack potato chips yang memiliki rasa yang enak dan unik, serta dapat memuaskan kebutuhan snacking setiap range usia khususnya millennials.. Japota, asli krenyesnya!.#JapotaMoment #AsliKrenyesnya

text: #TGIF ♥️ Valentine's Day is right around the corner but the only men we need is this spicy #umami Ramen 🍜🤣 . Today we will be announcing our lucky winner that will be scoring the ingredients to spice 🌶 💃  things up with this Spicy Korean Ramen Stir-Fry to share (or... not to share). Stay tuned for the winner... and enjoy this delicious dish inspo. 🍜 🍜 🍜 Spicy Korean Ramen Stir-FryServings:  1 to 2 Time: 20 minLevel: MediumIngredients* ½ cup leek, thinly sliced * ½ cup fennel bulb, thinly sliced * 1 cup assorted bell peppers, thinly sliced * 1 tbsp @eatluckyfoods Seoul “Gochujang” Korean Chili Pepper Paste* 1/2 cup @nonalimfoods Broth of choice (vegan Miso Ramen Broth or Spicy Chicken Ramen Bone Broth)* 1 heaping tbsp coconut cream (scooped from top of canned coconut meat or coconut butter) * 1 tsp minced garlic * ½ cup carrot, thinly sliced into ribbons with a carrot peeler * ¾ cup broccoli florets, cut into bite-sized pieces* ¼ cup peas, previously frozen* 1 sheet raw @SeaSnax nori, cut into skinny strips* ½ pouch Toasty Onion or Original #SeaSnax Chomperz* 1 pouch Nona Lim Laksa Rice Noodles * 3 tbsp Lucky Foods Seoul Spicy Vegan Kimchi * ½ avocado optional* Fresh cilantro optional * 1 tbsp olive oil, optional Instructions1. In a deep medium non-stick saucepan, saute leek for two minutes over medium heat with cooking spray until slightly browning then add fennel and saute for an additional 2 minutes. If sticking, add a splash of broth, then add peppers and lower heat to medium low.2. Cover and allow to cook for 5 minutes, uncovering to stir occasionally. 3. When peppers and fennel are caramelizing and browning, add broth of choice, chili paste, coconut cream, or oil and garlic.4. Combine well, and add broccoli. Simmer on medium low heat for 4 minutes, or until broccoli are bright green.5. Tear Laksa rice noodle package to vent and microwave for a minute6. Add peas and noodles and cook for 30 seconds7. Add SeaSnax raw nori for additional savory umami undertones. When ready to serve, drizzle with olive oil, and top with Kimchi, avocado slices and crunchy savory Chomperz. Dive in!!

text: // How To Tuesday // 🐟How to Make Seaweed Chips🐟Fun Fact: The chemical composition of #seaweed is so close to human blood plasma that they are excellent at regulating and purifying our blood.INGREDIENTS:12 nori sheets1/4 cup water1 T. sesame oil3 cloves garlic, mincedPinch ground cayenne pepperSalt to tasteDIRECTIONS:1⃣Preheat the oven to 275°F. Cover two large baking sheets with parchment paper or aluminum foil.2⃣Place six sheets of nori, shiny side up, on the baking sheet. With a pastry brush, lightly brush the shiny side of the nori with water, be sure to reach the edges, then carefully align another sheet of nori on top and press them together. Repeat with the remaining sheets until they are buddied up.3⃣Using kitchen shears or a sharp knife, cut the nori into one-inch strips, then cut those strips in half crosswise. You will end up with about 42 chips. Arrange the chips in a single layer on the baking sheets.4⃣In a small bowl, combine the garlic, sesame oil, and cayenne. Use the pastry brush to coat the top of the chips, then sprinkle generously with salt. Use your fingers to sprinkle sesame seeds across the tops of the chips.5⃣Place on the middle rack of the oven, and bake for 15-20 minutes. They will turn a deep, glossy green. Remove from the oven, taste, and sprinkle with salt if you like. Allow them to cool before eating for maximum crunch. Eat up & enjoy! 🐙#LCNHowToTuesday #HowToTuesday #seaweed #seaweedchips

@las_to4ka рецепт прост совсем: нори (те что для суши) режешь полосками или как тебе нра. Выкладываешь на противень, на пекарскую бумагу. Смазываешь полоски нори оливковым маслом (кисточкой или пальцами). Посыпаешься морской солью. Только немножко. Можно ещё перемешать оливковое масло с капелькой кунжутного - тоже вкусно, я попробовала оба варианта ) духовку на 175 градусов. Запекать минут 10. Вынуть, остудить и засунуть в контейнер с плотной крышкой.

text: Heine Max Olesen 🌊Funder af Sea Man Seaweed Chips “Jeg har mikset tangteknologien fra Østen med noget af det, vi kender fra Vesten og Europa. Vores chips er lavet på en base af blæretang og kartoffel, og vi har minimeret plastikindholdet i emballagen.Jeg elsker tang. Jeg kommer fra Grenå, hvor vi har det vildeste havmiljø. Jeg er nærmest opvokset på min morfars fiskerkutter, og har løbet rundt dernede hele mit liv.Vi har en uudnyttet ressource i havet, og de sidste 7 år har det været min passion og besættelse at lave noget med tang og få mere kendskab til tangen. Det skulle gerne inspirere andre til at lave alt muligt med tang. Vi har så meget kystlinje og noget af verdens bedste tang lige under havets overflade.Når du høster tangen, skal det gennem en forædlingsproces. Det skal tørres eller steges. Så får du al umamien. Tang er så rigt på umami, så når du blander det med noget, komplimenterer du de andre smage.Jeg har ikke lavet det her for sundhedens skyld, men for at det skulle være gourmet-oplevelse.Navnet. Ja, altså, når man siger det hurtigt lyder det jo som ’semen’. Men altså en ’sea man’ er jo betegnelsen for lowest man on deck. Ham, der er tættest på tangen. En hard working man. Og det er jeg. Jeg har været i gang med udviklingen af chipsene i et år, og så har vi været på markedet med det færdige produkt i et år, og det er helt vildt, hvor godt det går. Hver uge kommer der en efterspørgsel fra et nyt land. Det er helt sindssygt.” I weekenden var vi på Food Festival i Århus og mødte nogle af de mest interessante, danske fødevareproducenter lige nu. Blandt andet Heine. Hold godt øje med ham 🙏@seamanchips @foodfestivalofficial #tang #havet #lokalefødevarer #gourmet #chips #seaweedchips #iværksætter #anbefaling

text: Homemade Sesame Seaweed Chips ❤️Wanna try it? OMG We can’t stop eating these!! .芝麻海苔脆片要命了！吃了停不下來（好在不是高卡點心，吃多了也不會內疚😁）.Seaweed 14-16 sheets 海苔(for wrapping sushi)Sesames 白芝麻Soy sauce 醬油 8gOyster sauce 蠔油 8gMaltose 麥芽糖 85g Water 水 20gSugar 糖 10g.1️⃣ Mix everything except seaweed and sesame (medium low heat on the stove; JUST TO DISSOLVE THE SUGAR don’t need to boil it!!)所有材料（除了芝麻和海苔）混合，中小火煮到糖都溶解（不用煮開；糖化就可以了）.2️⃣ Turn off the heat until it cools down 關火後待涼.3️⃣ Spread thin layer of the sauce to two seaweed sheets and sprinkle the sesames on top of one sheet. 將兩片海苔上塗抹薄薄一層的醬料.4️⃣ Put the other sheet (sauce side down) on the top, and use roller to stick two sheets together. 在其中一片上灑芝麻（我還壓碎一些杏仁在上面）然後將另一片海苔（有醬料的面朝下）放在上面，然後用桿麵棍來回壓緊.5️⃣ Cut the seaweeds into small pieces and bake the chips 250F for 15-18 minutes. 再把海苔片剪成小片，烤箱250度F烤約15-18分鐘 .. 🔸I used cookie cooling racks to bake the chips (so I don’t have to worry about flipping the chips in between baking time. If you are baking on the flat baking sheet, you might need to flip the chips after 8 minutes) 我用放涼餅乾的網架來烤，這樣底部也能同時烘烤。如果你沒有網架而是直接放在烤盤上烤，建議在烤前八分鐘後將海苔片翻面繼續烤）.#helendesignfood #bakeathome #healthylifestyle #healthydesserts #healthychips #seaweedchips #lowcalorierecipes #homemadechips #海苔片 #芝麻海苔脆片

text: •Kale & Seaweed Chips Dinner tonight was a repeat, so I wanted to show you a quick nutritions snack that’s perfect for after nap, before dinner time. My daughter has been loving these kale and seaweed chips I make. They couldn’t be any easier. It’s a super fun snack for kids bc of the crunch, and they are getting so many great vitamins (b12) and calcium, and iron. ...I rip the kale into chunks, they can be big chunks because it shrinks and they are so thin and crispy, and I cut the Nori with some scissors into little squares. I recently bought this oil and it’s perfect to add a little crisp. A pour a little on my hands and make sure the front and backs are coated well.  Add a little sprinkle of sea salt and bake at 375 for about 10 mns. Until crispy.

text: Throughout history people have flocked to coastal areas for food. Foraging for food can be rewarding here.Even if I don’t catch any fish I often forage for seaweed when I’m on the coast.I normally use it as an ingredient with pasta either blanched or fried. Last time I wanted to do something else with it so I made chips out of it.It’s very easy to make and it tastes great. Seaweed contains a high amount of iodine which can be healthy for you. Many people suffer from iodine deficiency so in that sense it can be very beneficial. Just make sure you don’t eat too much of it too often. The high amount of iodine can cause iodine poisoning. And beware not to eat it at all if you have Metabolic disorder. That said it also contains both vitamins A, B, C, E and K as well a big variety of minerals, amino acids and omega-3s.If you want to try making seaweed chips here’s an easy recipe for you:The only ingredients you need are: Seaweed, Virgin olive oil and Sea saltStart by cutting the top shoots into bite sized pieces. Pour a few spoons of virgin olive oil in a bowl, toss the seaweed around in it and add some sea salt to it. Take out the seaweed and let the oil drip off before you spread it out on a baking tray. Put it in a preheated oven at 100 degrees C for about an hour and voilà.#undepend #bushcraft #survival #wildernesssurvival #outdoor #primitivesurvival #survivalism #primitiveskills #intothewoods #getoutside #outdoorsman #bushcraftdk #wildernesscamping #wildcamping #foraging #nature #wildfood #shtf #prepping #hunter #huntergatherer #firemaking #survivalskills #primitivefire #wilderness #seaweed #seaweedchips #survivalcraft #survivalcraft #ig_scandinavia

text: 🤍🖤🤍🖤...Better Together 🖤🤍🖤🤍...Chungmu gimbap is a branch of the gimbap family, whose name comes from the southern cost town of Chungmu, now Tongyeong City in Korea. Unlike most other types of gimbap, Chungmu gimbap consists of finger-sized rice-only rolls served with marinated squid in red pepper sauce and radish kimchi. Though the recipe seems simple, there are not many restaurants in Seoul selling Chungmu gimbap, and many people agree that the best Chungmu gimbap is made in Tongyeong (Chungmu). text: "Tuna" sandwich ! 😲 Yes indeedy!And it tastes like the real thing! 👌🏾 This recipe serves 4.Ingredients: ciabatta bread,  2/3 of a can of green or young jackfruit, 1/2 can of chickpeas, 3 sticks of celery, 1/4 of a white onion, 3 tablespoons of hummus, fresh cracked black pepper, a pinch of salt, a splash of apple cider vinegar, and 1/2 a package of roasted seaweed snacks/chips. Recipe:Thoroughly rinse the jackfruit at least three times. Cut off the tough part on one end. Shred the Jackfruit and remove the seeds with your hands. Thoroughly rinse the chickpeas at least three times, then smash them on a cutting board; they should still be recognizable. Combine the two ingredients together. Form the mixture into medium-to-large sized balls, then squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Put it in the refrigerator until you're ready to use it.Dice your celery and onions into very small pieces. Shred up your seaweed snacks. Add these ingredients to a bowl with the Jackfruit and smashed chickpeas. Add your hummus, black pepper, salt, and apple cider vinegar. Stir the ingredients until everything is evenly distributed. Taste the mixture to make sure it is well seasoned. You can use vegan mayonnaise instead of hummus. You can substitute the apple cider vinegar for lemon juice.Toast your bread on both sides with your choice of oil in a non-stick pan or cast iron skillet. Spread your tuna salad on to the bread, then eat! This recipe took about 20 to 30 minutes for me to prepare. Ideally it should have been done when I wasn't starving LOL. It definitely hit the spot! The bonus for me was the fact that I still got in my carbs, protein, and fiber. I hope you try it out 😀. #jackfruit#chickpeas #ciabatta /#ciabattabread#celery #onions #blackpepper#salt#hummus#applecidervinegar #seaweedsnacks / #seaweedchips#vegantuna#vegan

text: 👋 We are getting really good at exercising our dipping skills... How bout you?Need something new to dip? Try Chomperz with this “cheesy” #whole30athome Spinach Artichoke dip and let us know what you think!Healthy Spinach & Artichoke Dip Ingredients:2 cups frozen, or drained jarred artichoke hearts 1 leek, ½ cup cleaned and chopped 2 cups loosely packed fresh spinach ½ tsp minced garlic 2 tbsp ghee @fourthandheart4 tbsp nutritional yeast Sea Salt to taste (will vary depending on if artichoke hearts already contained salt)Method:In a medium frying pan, heat ghee on medium high heat and then saute leek and artichoke hearts for 10 minutes (less time if artichokes were previously marinated). Add spinach, lower heat to low, saute and cover for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Once spinach is wilted, add sea salt to taste and nutritional yeast. Stir well then carefully scoop mixture into a small blender or food processor, and pulse until well mixed, but still chunky. Enjoy with Chomperz, or use in replace of tuna fish in a raw SeaSnax nori wrap!

text: Dulse (Palmaria palmata) is one of my favourite seaweeds and I'll be teaching it this weekend! It gives a great salty, umami flavour to bread, dips and so much more. .Have you ever harvested fresh dulse? It's also beautiful to look at in the water! This Sunday participants will get to try dulse fresh, dried and in bread. You'll get to see it in situ and learn where it likes to grow, how to sustainably harvest it and how to dry and store it..Dulse is packed with nutrition, is high in protein, vitamin A and iron. It also contains potassium, B vitamins, calcium and manganese. I share more about it, including recipes in my #seaweedbook  and plenty more in the flesh on Sunday's course. Details and how to book on my website. .Meanwhile here's a dulse recipe for you.Baba Ghanoush with Dulse Seaweed.An Arabian dish perfect for dipping freshly cut vegetables into, or spreading onto bread. Inspired by Daverick Leggett's recipe and given a seaweed twist..Ingredients3 aubergines3 cloves of garlic2 tbsp dark tahiniJuice of 2 lemonsSea salt and pepper to taste5 g dried and ground dulse seaweedOlive oil to garnish and to tasteBurn the aubergines. Either on the highest temperature in the oven or on an open flame until they go soft and squidgy. Scoop out the insides, or peel off the skin and blend the flesh with the rest of the ingredients. Drizzle with a good olive oil and serve. Lasts well for a week, if you hide it and don’t eat it all at once.

text: 👩‍🍳 This year, give Grandma's Green Bean Casserole something to talk about. Packed with flavor, and topped with crunchy wheat-free toasty onion Chomperz, we guarantee your friends and family will love this dairy-free, soy-free spin on this classic dish. Share this post in your stories for extra bonus points for this week’s giveaway with Coconut Secret! Vegan Green Bean Casserole 🥘4 Servings Ingredients: 1 heaping tsp minced garlic (1 large clove)12 oz trimmed green beans½ cup low sodium vegetable broth 3 tbsp @coconutsecretofficial Aminos 1 tbsp olive oil ½-1 bag Onion ChomperzHeat a pan to medium heat. Add ½ cup broth* and 2 tbsp coconut aminos. Bring to a slow boil and add green beans. Stir for 1 minute and then cover for 1 minute to allow beans to steam. Uncover, add minced garlic, and 1 tbsp coconut aminos. Continue to saute until beans are al dente (about 2-5 minutes on medium heat). *Note: For a thicker glaze, start with only ¼ cup broth and add more as needed. When beans are a bright green and can be pierced with a fork, (careful not to allow them to get soggy), toss with olive oil. Plate and serve hot or room temperature. When ready to serve, take onion Chomperz and use clean hands to “crinkle” them over the onions for a umami, savory, salty, crunchy topping.

text: iHerb購入品🍀スクショも使って失礼😅...だいぶ前に届いてたんですけど、体調不良が続きなかなかpostできませんでした😣今回二度目でブラシ以外食品で、ほとんど食べてしまいパッケージしかない😂で、スクショも使わせていただきました😅..⭐Stoneridge Orchards: ダークチョコ・ディップ・ストロベリー🍫🍓YouTuberのあいかさん @aica_cosmeblog さんおすすめ品☝️最近🍓味をすすんで食べているので、日本でも🍓のチョコはたくさんあるけど、こういうのはなかなかないので、食べごたえもあってリピ決定❗.⭐Natierra: オーガニック フリーズドライ ストロベリー🍓こちらもYouTuberの佐々木あさひさん @asahisasaki が中性脂肪値に効く❓とかでiHerbで買えないときはAmazonでいろいろ試してました☝️今は体調悪くても食欲は落ちないので体重増えてしまいましたけど、一時体重キープにも役立ってた気がします🤔でも、中性脂肪値には効いてはいないかな😣あれ❓もしかして食べ過ぎ❓iHerbではもう一つのメーカーのもあるんですけど売り切れが多いですね😅iHerbで取り扱ってる物が食べやすくて美味しいですね☝️.⭐Real Techniques by Samantha Chapman: Limited Edition Metallic Dimension Brush Kit 5 Piece Kit.リアルテクニクスのブラジルは一度は使ってみたいと思っていて、YouTuberのmilkypinkさん @milkypinkrose の購入品動画でのキラキラ✨に惹かれて買ってしまいました🤩アイメイクブラシ２本、パウダーブラシ２本、パレットのセットです☝️ピンク、オレンジ、パープルがキラキラなブラシセットです✨✨.⭐Choco love: アーモンド シーソルト インダークチョコレート🍫こちらもあいかさんおすすめ☝️塩入りも間違いなく美味しいです😋.⭐Endangered Spices Chocolate: エスプレッソビーンズ+ダークチョコレート🍫チョコラブがほとんど売り切れだったので、似たような板チョコをセレクト。コーヒー味もいい😋.⭐Endangered Spices Chocolate: タルトラズベリー+ダークチョコレートバー🍫ラズベリーの味はあまり感じないけど、普通に美味しいです😋.⭐Snyder's: ミニプレッツェルプレッツェルも大好きでアメリカならあるかなと検索したらありました☝️大容量で美味しい😋これもリピ決定❗チョコもね😁.⭐California Gold Nutrition: オメガ800サントリーのDHA＆EPA+セサミンを飲んでたんですけど、高くてなかなか続けられなくて😣他を切りつめればいい話なんですけど、iHerbはサプリも豊富なのでこちらを選んでみました。YouTuberのMisstoxicことえみさん @misstoxicxxx も飲まれていますよ☝️粒は大きいけど、安いです‼️こちらはどちらにするか迷い中です😅.⭐Seapoint Farms: 海藻ポテトチップス かぼちゃゴマ、 アーモンドセサミこちらもあさひさんおすすめ☝️日本にもありそうな味だけど、しょっぱすぎず美味しいです😋こちらもリピ😁..もう次に注文しようとカートにはリピ&その他チョコがいっぱいです😁また早く食べたい‼️#食#チョコレート#フリーズドライいちご#サプリメント#メイクブラシ #海藻チップス#chocolate#freezedried #supplements #makeup#makeupbrushes #seaweedchips #iherb#メイク好きな人と繋がりたい

text: SEAGULHai teman-teman kita ada produk BARU loh! Namanya SEAGUL singkatan dari SEAweed GULung. SEAGUL merupakan snack rumput laut yang diproduksi oleh Celine Kitchen dan siap untuk menjangkau seluruh masyarakat INDONESIA. SEAGUL dibuat menggunakan rumput laut yang berkualitas tinggi , selain itu rumput laut juga mempunyai banyak manfaat dan sudah sangat populer sejak jaman dahulu. Sejak 300 tahun sebelum Masehi , rumput laut telah dikonsumsi di Asia timur sebagai lauk sehari-hari dan untuk mengobati penyakit. Rumput laut mengandung beragam nutrisi , seperti karbohidrat , protein , serat , vitamin dan mineral termasuk magnesium , mangan , yodium , kalium , sodium , kalsium , folat , zat besi , dan tembaga, dalam jumlah yang cukup tinggi. Nutrisi yang terkandung di dalam rumput laut menjadikannya sebagai cemilan yang tidak hanya lezat , tetapi juga sehat. Selain itu rumput laut juga tergolong makanan yang rendah kalori sehingga cocok untuk teman-teman yang sedang DIET nih. SEAGUL cocok banget untuk menemani teman-teman saat bersantai , nonton , kongkow-kongkow sama teman atau lagi kerja depan komputer. SEAGUL tuh snack rumput laut yang nagihin banget deh , rasanya yang CRUNCHY dengan kombinasi rasa yang PAS sehingga banyak disukai oleh berbagai kalangan , dari anak kecil sampai orang tua pun semuanya PASTI SUKA dan bikin KETAGIHAN untuk ngemilin terus. SEAGUL tersedia dengan berbagai macam rasa seperti ORIGINAL yang gurih dan SPICY untuk teman-teman yang suka banget sama pedas dan juga SEAGUL ini HALAL & VEGETARIAN FRIENDLY loh. text: #Repost @raw_by_nature_ (@get_repost)・・・VERDENS FØRSTE TANG TORTILLA CHIPS Vi har glædet os til at dele dette, for det er en stor nyhed.Nu fås velsmagende sprøde tortilla chips med tang. De første i Danmark der har smagt dem var overraskede over, at der rent faktisk er tang i. De kunne nærmest ikke smage forskel. Disse tangchips er lavet med 35% næringsrig og bæredygtigt tang. De er glutenfrie og næringsrige, og den grønne farve du kan se når du swiper er såmænd bare fra spinat-pulver. Tang er noget af det mest sunde og bæredygtige du kan spise og er bla. rig på jod. Disse nye chips er fulde af smag og kommer i 3 varianter. De er så nye at de ikke er landet på hylderne derude endnu. Vi starter snart ud med én smag (original). text: Oh haiii. So many of you inquired about this savory recipe I wrote at work for a hot lil date night so here you are and #TGIF 💃🏼 🍜 🌶 👩‍🍳 See note from me below. Spicy Korean Ramen Stir-FryServings:  1 to 2 Time: 20 minLevel: MediumIngredients* ½ cup leek, thinly sliced * ½ cup fennel bulb, thinly sliced * 1 cup assorted bell peppers, thinly sliced * 1 tbsp @eatLuckyFoods Seoul “Gochujang” Korean Chili Pepper Paste* 1/2 cup @NonaLimFoods Broth of choice (vegan Miso Ramen Broth or Spicy Chicken Ramen Bone Broth)* 1 heaping tbsp coconut cream (scooped from top of canned coconut meat or coconut butter) * 1 tsp minced garlic * ½ cup carrot, thinly sliced into ribbons with a carrot peeler * ¾ cup broccoli florets, cut into bite-sized pieces* ¼ cup peas, previously frozen* 1 sheet raw @SeaSnax nori, cut into skinny strips* ½ pouch Toasty Onion or Original #SeaSnax Chomperz* 1 pouch Nona Lim Laksa Rice Noodles * 3 tbsp Lucky Foods Seoul Spicy Vegan Kimchi * ½ avocado optional* Fresh cilantro optional * 1 tbsp olive oil, optional Instructions1. In a deep medium non-stick saucepan, saute leek for two minutes over medium heat with cooking spray until slightly browning then add fennel and saute for an additional 2 minutes. If sticking, add a splash of broth, then add peppers and lower heat to medium low.2. Cover and allow to cook for 5 minutes, uncovering to stir occasionally. 3. When peppers and fennel are caramelizing and browning, add broth of choice, chili paste, coconut cream, or oil and garlic.4. Combine well, and add broccoli. Simmer on medium low heat for 4 minutes, or until broccoli are bright green.5. Tear Laksa rice noodle package to vent and microwave for a minute6. Add peas and noodles and cook for 30 seconds7. Add SeaSnax raw nori for additional savory umami undertones. When ready to serve, drizzle with olive oil, and top with Kimchi, avocado slices and crunchy savory Chomperz. Dive in!! Notes to Lauren-ify.To make it soy-free— sub soy ingredients for coconut aminos. To make it grain-free— sub noodles for Zoodles and scratch the Chomperz. But these Nona Lim rice noodles are super clean and Chomperz are bomb so...👌.

text: .*Day 29 Celiac Awareness Month*.I love drinking water with chiaseeds in it. My mil taught me to drink this when it's hot as it helps with hydration, they absorp upto 10 times their weight in water and form a gelatinous coating around the seeds so it's quite a weird texture to drink.Chiaseeds are rich in Omega3 fatty acids, fiber, protein, calcium, iron, and magnesium. They also contain vitamins B1 and B3 and high in antioxidants. So it's really good to add to your diet when glutenfree and vegetarian :)This time I've added them in coconut water as it's full of electrolytes, perfect drink to hydrate yourself after a dogwalk in this heat..I got some seaweed with green tea chips from the Chinese store in Antwerp which I opened today. I never tried them before so I was very curious. It's​ nice and crispy but I can understand that not everyone would like this, the taste is quite strong. It contains vitamins A & C and is a source of calcium too. But most important one is that it contains iodine, a nutrient you hardly find in other food. Heaving enough iodine is important it seems to maintain a healthy thyroid.It's also high in antioxidants which prevents inflammation, good for people with Celiac Disease if they get glutened like me recently :).#glutenfree #chiaseeds #seaweed #seaweedchips #celiacawarenessmonth #coeliakiemaand #healthy #delicious #glutenfreefood #glutenfreebaking #homebaking #glutenfreeindia #india #incredibleindia #igramming_india #glutenfreemumbai #foodtalkindia #mumbaifoodie #mumbaifoodlovers #mumbaifoodcrush #mumbai #mymumbai #mumbai_igers #foodieinmumbai #trellingfood #glutenfreeliving #glutenvrij #coeliakie #celiac #whatceliacseat

text: Wild seaweed sushi and rice balls. Cheering myself up with sharing food with friends and planning festive snacks and meals. We even played pictionary last night - the perfect way to have a laugh and come together! Need I say more?!🥣This recipe is from my book 'Seaweed Foraging in Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly' where I  also describe how to harvest and dry seaweed. You can order the book from my website. 🥢This recipe uses laver/nori/porphyra, though I've also successfully done these with gutweed/sea lettuce/ulva.My world revolves around, people, food and nature. These are the things that nourish me, and wild, foraged food ticks all those boxes for me. 🍄Wishing you all a nourishing weekend; coming together to celebrate the important things in life - love, care and respect. These things still and always will matter. Xxx

text: ⁠Did you know over 12,000 species of seaweed have been identified to date? That's a lot of different seaweeds to try!⁠⁠Here at 12 Tides, our seaweed snacks feature sugar kelp (saccharina latissima), which is a native species to the cool, clean waters of the Northern Atlantic and Northern Pacific oceans. Like all seaweeds, kelp provides a wealth of protein, fiber, and best of all - FLAVOR. 😋⁠⁠That umami-like taste people love so much, is best paired with simple ingredients and flavors that help accentuate it. Our personal favorites are sea salt, chili, and a special 'everything' mixture we created. text: How to get your kids to eat veggie heavy meals...involve them! 12 days of salads: sushi roll salad! Tastes just like sushi! #bestkids #gettheminvolved #vegan #sushi #salad #edemame #carrots #sesamecrusted #tofu #jasminerice #oystermushrooms #seaweedchips #soy #pickledginger #greengreengreen #eattherainbow #vegansalad #plantbased #vegansofig #veganmomma #healthyfamily #healthymomlife #momlife #lovethem #veganfoodie #foodpic #recipeincluded #enjoy *Recipe*TofuBlack or white sesame seedsSesame oil Soy Sauce EdamameOsyster mushroomsPickled ginger Jasmine or basmati riceSeaweed chipsBaby greensTake a handful of greens, top with carrots and pickled ginger.Cook a cup of rice as directed. Heat skillet w a tsp of sesame oil. Sauté mushrooms on one side and edamame on the other half of skillet for 3 minutes. Take edemame out and put a top salad. Turn over mushrooms, cook another 3 minutes. Place mushrooms a top salad. Drain firm tofu, cut into strips and marinate in soy sauce for 2mns. Crust two sides w sesame seeds. Brown the sesame crusted sides of the tofu in the heated oiled skillet. Once both sides are browned nicely remove and add to salad. Add a scoop of cooked rice and top with seaweed chips and drizzle soy sauce (from left over marinade) and sesame oil to taste, ENJOY!

text: Long Post.. School started back for us yesterday, and since school is only in three days ,I didn’t see the purpose of cooking just for three days because I honestly don’t know how to cook small amounts for my meal prep. @yasminebianca_ gave me kale salad recipe and I was excited to use , but I went to three different Walmarts and they were all out of kale and I was so upset so I just came home and made a “vegetarian potluck.” Everything I use the week before from my sweet potato tacos was included , plus I threw in some Jackfruit, I added some rice I need to finish I already had opened and threw it on a bed of spinach with tomatoes , with the mixed nuts and called it a day. If you swipe to my last picture you’ll see a picture of my lunch how it turned out yesterday and it was absolutely amazing! The pictures in between are my snacks and you can see I just threw everything in one bag.  my goal for this year is to just have a simple meal plan. I have been doing really well with intermittent fasting and its been teaching me great things. But overall my goal this year is just to keep my lunch and snacks really simple so if can’t fit in this bag for the week it’s not going. So my middle picture is just three days worth of months and three days worth of snacks thrown into this bag. I plan on taking every Monday and it  that’s it for the week. #agirlsgottaeatright💪🏾 #mealprep #vegetarian #jackjack #sweetpotato #seaweedchips #seasalt #intermittentfasting

text: Interesting! How do you make them?

hi @thesingaporewomensweekly.. i gt this idea from an online recipe.☺️i used 1 pkt of popiah skin, 1 pkt of seaweed, 1-2 egg/s and oil for frying. steps: break egg and mix. spread 1 popiah skin and brush egg evenly on it. 'paste' the seaweed sheets on the popiah skin. brush egg on the seaweed layer then 'paste' another popiah skin on it. cut it into the shapes that u like. repeat steps. fry on medium flame.😊

text: Did you know seaweed is a natural source of iodine?⁠⁠Iodine is a mineral the body needs to make thyroid hormones. These hormones are used to control the body's metabolism as well as to support proper bone and brain development. Idoine is especially critical for women during pregnancy and infancy. 🤰⁠⁠So, the next time you're looking for a healthy snack, don't hesitate to reach for seaweed! Just make sure the seaweed snack you grab is one of the good ones. We recommend our Puffed Seaweed Chips. text: 豆もやしとキャベツのナムル🥬﻿﻿太陽に当たることなく育つことから、ひ弱な表現に使われるもやし君。﻿﻿そもそも、もやしって植物名じゃないのですね。﻿﻿実は一番流通している豆の付いていない＂もやし＂は、名称としては「ブラックマッペ」が正解(笑)﻿﻿今日使った＂大豆もやし＂は「豆もやし」という名前を持っています。﻿﻿ちなみに＂もやし＂の定義から言うと、ブロッコリースプラウトやかいわれ大根も入ってきます👍﻿﻿見た目はひ弱なイメージだけど、豆にはないビタミンCやビタミンB群、疲労回復に効果的なアスパラギン酸、カリウム、カルシウム、鉄などを含んだ栄養価の高い野菜です💡﻿﻿(参考：野菜の便利帳)﻿﻿私は、せっかくならたんぱく質も欲しいので豆もやしを使用しています♪ ﻿﻿【材料】﻿・豆もやし﻿・キャベツ﻿・ジャバン海苔(韓国のりフレーク)﻿・白いりごま ﻿﻿【調味料】﻿・昆布だし﻿・ごま油﻿﻿豆もやしはサッと(10秒ほど)湯通しして、流水ですぐに熱をとります。﻿キャベツ(生のまま)、豆もやしに調味料を混ぜ合わせて完成🙌﻿ごま、のりフレークは最後にたっぷりかけます♪﻿﻿ちなみに、ごまは早いうちに混ぜると底に、海苔はボールの壁面に付きます。。﻿﻿キャベツがほんの少し、塩気でしっとりし始めたら食べ時です✨﻿﻿のりフレークは色んな所で売っていますが、Costcoで売っているこの商品が一番美味しい❣️﻿(他の製品は生臭さがあったり...しっくり来なかったです。)﻿﻿#簡単おつまみ﻿#ナムル﻿#ヴィーガンおつまみ﻿#ビーガンおつまみ﻿#ヴィーガン﻿#ビーガン﻿#ヴィーガンレシピ ﻿#ビーガンレシピ﻿#ヴィーガン料理﻿#ビーガン料理﻿#ジャバンのり﻿#韓国海苔﻿#のりフレーク﻿#コストコ﻿#コストコ購入品﻿#大豆もやし﻿#豆もやし﻿#vegan﻿#koreanfood ﻿#namul ﻿#seaweed ﻿#seaweedchips ﻿#heathy ﻿#healthyfood ﻿#yummy ﻿#yummyfood#kanadian_副菜#kanadian_おつまみ #kanadian_ビール

text: Honesty hour: I have been emotionally eating like crazy since Isaiah left. Sooooo I decided Monday to only eat food that nourishes me because the junk is not not going help make me feel any better. I've been home 🏡 a lot and wanting to just eat everything salty today so I grabbed these #seaweedchips instead. Ok, they aren't like regular chips but they did give me the salty crunchiness I was craving. And even better, I don't feel bad about eating these. text: Chocks away for the Bank Holiday! We'll be sprinkling our Seaspoon wonderfood from start to finish, to make sure that all our meals are packed with nutrition, even the treatiest treats! First up, these tempting halloumi fries didn't stick around for long... HALLOUMI & SEAWEED FRIES· 225 g Halloumi (1 packet)· Cornflour· 1 teaspoon Seaspoon Seaweed Boost· Runny honey· Black and white sesame seeds , toasted for 10 mins in ovenSlice the halloumi into thick chip shapes and dust all over in cornflour.  Heat frying pan with some oil and shallow fry the halloumi, in 2 batches, until crispy and brown on all sides. Meanwhile heat the runny honey and Seaspoon Seaweed Boost in the microwave for 30-60 seconds, until hot. Serve fries with honey mix drizzled over and finish with sesame seeds scattered on top.#seasweed #seaspoon #seaweedisgoodforyou #halloumi #seaweedchips #seaweedsnacks #bankholiday #vegetarianrecipe

text: Welcome, welcome to all who've started following me in the last couple of weeks and hello to all those who continue to travel with me..I'm a forager who loves to teach people about the bounty that nature provides, to help people to see the hedgerows and coastline with new eyes and give you a new layer of understanding of the landscape around us. Sustainability and minimal impact are important to me and easy to practice when you know a few basics. .This photo was taken by @karen.pirieof @cornwallwoman after Karen spent 3 hours with me on a seaweed foraging course learning about the flavours, versatility and nutrition of British seaweeds. Our group started by seeing a sea (excuse the pun) of weeds and ended up with a list of ingredients and recipes - that gives me such pleasure!..If you like to listen to snippets from that seaweed foraging course and hear an interview I did with Karen about seaweeds then you can listen to her podcast here -  www.wildwalks-southwest.co.uk/blog/seaweed-foraging/.Next year's foraging courses are now on my website calendar. Just follow the link in my bio to find out more.

Guten Abend ihr Lieben, kennt ihr die Seaman Chips von @seamanchips? Wer #sushi mag wird diese #seaweedchips lieben 😏! In Asien ist dieser #snack schon sehr beliebt und auch hier wird er langsam beliebter. In Asien besteht der Snack nur aus #noriblättern. text: SEAWEED CHIPS with NUTS ❣️🌱healthy low carb snacking that is satisfying 😄🙌🙌🙌 There is so much goodness packed into this portable snack. 🌱🌱🌱Seaweed offers the broadest range of minerals of any food on the planet, containing 10-20 times the mineral concentration of land plants, plus it’s high in protein and fiber. That’s why a serving can be only 25-100 calories and packed with flavor and nutrients. 🌱It's an excellent source of iodine, vitamin A & K and a very good source of folate, magnesium, iron, and calcium. 🌱Seaweed also contains measurable amounts of vitamins C and E, which help the absorption of all the other good stuff. 🌱It satisfies a salty craving and helps many people reap the benefits of sea vegetables who otherwise would not. ✳️I usually munch on RAW NUTS because roasting them may alter and damage the polyunsaturated fats that nuts contain which is vulnerable to oxidation! Roasted nuts are yum so don't eliminate themtotally❣️the heart healthy monounsaturated fats remain intact as this fat can tolerate higher temperatures 🙌🙌 I store my nuts in the fridge or freezer for freshness to prevent rancidity. Rancid oils are pro-inflammatory and carcinogenic. The more the surface of the nut is exposed to air, the more likely it will be to oxidise. Roasted, chopped, and ground nuts go rancid more quickly than whole raw ones.#lowcarbsnack #seaweedchips #nuts #almonds #wholefoods #realfood #nutrition #satisfying #paleo #vegan#weightlossfood #fitfood #fitfoodie #jroguljfood #instafoodpic #instafoodporn #instahealthysnacks #instahealthybody #instafitfam #instablogger #instainspire #instagram #instadaily #nutritionist

text: SEAGULHai teman-teman kita ada produk BARU loh! Namanya SEAGUL singkatan dari SEAweed GULung. SEAGUL merupakan snack rumput laut yang diproduksi oleh Celine Kitchen dan siap untuk menjangkau seluruh masyarakat INDONESIA. SEAGUL dibuat menggunakan rumput laut yang berkualitas tinggi , selain itu rumput laut juga mempunyai banyak manfaat dan sudah sangat populer sejak jaman dahulu. Sejak 300 tahun sebelum Masehi , rumput laut telah dikonsumsi di Asia timur sebagai lauk sehari-hari dan untuk mengobati penyakit. Rumput laut mengandung beragam nutrisi , seperti karbohidrat , protein , serat , vitamin dan mineral termasuk magnesium , mangan , yodium , kalium , sodium , kalsium , folat , zat besi , dan tembaga, dalam jumlah yang cukup tinggi. Nutrisi yang terkandung di dalam rumput laut menjadikannya sebagai cemilan yang tidak hanya lezat , tetapi juga sehat. Selain itu rumput laut juga tergolong makanan yang rendah kalori sehingga cocok untuk teman-teman yang sedang DIET nih. SEAGUL cocok banget untuk menemani teman-teman saat bersantai , nonton , kongkow-kongkow sama teman atau lagi kerja depan komputer. SEAGUL tuh snack rumput laut yang nagihin banget deh , rasanya yang CRUNCHY dengan kombinasi rasa yang PAS sehingga banyak disukai oleh berbagai kalangan , dari anak kecil sampai orang tua pun semuanya PASTI SUKA dan bikin KETAGIHAN untuk ngemilin terus. SEAGUL tersedia dengan berbagai macam rasa seperti ORIGINAL yang gurih dan SPICY untuk teman-teman yang suka banget sama pedas dan juga SEAGUL ini HALAL & VEGETARIAN FRIENDLY loh. Yuk rasakan nikmatnya SEAGUL , teman-teman dapat memesannya melalui WA di 085693169989 atau klik link di bio !#seaweed #snackseaweed #seaweedsnacks #seaweedsnack #seaweedchips #snackvegetarian #seagul #seaguloriginal #seagulspicy #celinekitchen #homemade #vegetarianfood #veganfood #jualmakananvegetarian #vegetarian #kulinervegan #kulinervegetarian #vegetarianindonesia #vegetarianjakarta #veganindonesia #veganjakarta

text: Forget Potato Chips🙌🏼 Try Seaweed Crisps instead! You can either use it as a side dish or eat it up straight as a snack🖤Tastes exactly like fried fish!!SEAWEED CRISPS Ingredients-Seaweed(Nori) Paper-Glutinous rice flour-Salt-Chilli Powder-Cinnamon Powder-Water -Oil -Sesame SeedsProcess-In a bowl add glutinous rice flour,a pinch of salt,a pinch of chilli powder and cinnamon powder(Rice flour mixture)-Add a cup of water and mix until no lumps-Heat a pan and after the pan is heated add the mixture prepared earlier(rice flour mixture)-Stir and cook until the mixture is thick and forms a doughy texture(Low flame)-Let it chill (mixture)-Take a seaweed paper and apply the paste of mixture on both sides and sprinkle sesame seeds-Heat a pan and add oil (half a cup) -Gently place the seaweed covered with rice paste and deep fry in a low flame(Golden brown)-Seaweed Chip will be ready!! text: Memorial Day Umami Meatballs.🍝 🍝 🍝Craving meatballs but looking to avoid the added bread crumbs, cheese, milk, and eggs while also adding bold savory flavors and getting in healthy fiber and nutrients? This fast and flavorful dish is PACKED with umami flavor and only takes a few moments to prep! It’s the perfect appetizer to bring to a backyard barbecue this weekend. Even if everyone is 6 feet apart. 🙃 Makes 8 meatballs Serves 2Ingredients: 1/2 pound grass-fed ground beef (or a meatless ground option) 1/4 cup peeled zucchini, grated on a cheese grater1/2 bag, or 1/2 cup Chomperz, in flavor of choice (smashed into crumbs) We used Barbecue1 pack Chipotle @SeaSnax (Small pack), torn into pieces Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a mixing bowl, loosely mix together all SeaSnax and veggies before adding in ground beef. Use clean hands to fold the ingredients together until generally well combined and then divide into 8 portions and set out on a clean plate. Using hands, roll each portion into a ball and replace on plate. Wash hands. Heat small frying pan to medium heat and add cooking spray or high quality butter. Delicately place each meatball onto pan and sear for 12 seconds and flip with tongs. Repeat with each meatball and then transfer to a non stick baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes or until each meatball is no longer pink in center. Enjoy when ready! Tag a friend that would enjoy this recipe!

text: VERDENS FØRSTE TANG TORTILLA CHIPS Vi har glædet os til at dele dette, for det er en stor nyhed.Nu fås velsmagende sprøde tortilla chips med tang. De første i Danmark der har smagt dem var overraskede over, at der rent faktisk er tang i. De kunne nærmest ikke smage forskel. Disse tangchips er lavet med 35% næringsrig og bæredygtigt tang. De er glutenfrie og næringsrige, og den grønne farve du kan se når du swiper er såmænd bare fra spinat-pulver. Tang er noget af det mest sunde og bæredygtige du kan spise og er bla. rig på jod. Disse nye chips er fulde af smag og kommer i 3 varianter. De er så nye at de ikke er landet på hylderne derude endnu. Vi starter snart ud med én smag (original). Hvor vil du elske at kunne købe dem? 😋#nyhed #tangchips #chips #tang #iseachips #seaweed #seaweedchips #seamore #yum #treat #glutenfri #glutenfree #rawbynature

text: @bowld.sl not only delivered, but it IMPRESSED!Service is fast, food delicious and the space relaxed and unpretentious. You should definitely check them out!Located down Sea View Avenue in Colpetty, the signature dishes of this healthy and wholesome ‘fast food’ restaurant are #PokeBowls and ‘Nana Bowls. They also serve a few appetizers, one dessert and a small selection of drinks. When ordering, you can pick a starch base for their #poke dishes including #sushirice, red rice, #zoodles or go half ‘n’ half!I picked the latter in a mix of sushi rice and zoodles topped with Spicy #Salmon (photographed portion - small) with #sashimisalmon, spicy soy, #edamame, cucumbers, tomatoes, onion, avocado, tobiko, #wakame, wonton crisps and wasabi mayo. And it was just the right kind of spicy with a lot of play on texture and layers of fresh flavors!I also tasted the Tangy #Tuna (photographed portion - small) with #sashimituna, passionfruit soy, mango, green chilli, onion, red cabbage, #tobiko, panko, shredded #seaweed and chilli mayo). It tasted a lot like the spicy tuna maki rolls at popular sushi restaurants, with the passion fruit rendering that extra burst of savor!I also tried a portion of the #pokenachos which served crisp and crunchy tempura-battered #seaweedchips, topped with both minced tuna and salmon sashimi marinated in spicy soy, tobiko, panko, spring onion and a dressing of #wasabimayo. Again great play on texture and full of flavour.The #CoconutPannaCotta finished with a Watermelon and Lime Granita was not my kind of dessert. I liked the flavour of toasted coconut flakes but I didn’t like the watermelon and coconut milk combination all that much.#Bowld offers both indoor and outdoor dining in a cozy, homey settings and serves flavour bombs in bowls that are a #ColomboMustTry! Now I can’t wait to go back and dig into one of their #NanaBowls!...They have options for Vegans and Vegetarians too; one of them is the #TeriyakiEggplant with sweet corn, carrot, onion, red bell pepper, shredded seaweed, #WantonCrisps and Chilli Mayo. The restaurant also only uses #bamboostraws with their drinks in an effort to be more environmentally sustainable.

text: World Food Day! We zullen anders met ons voedsel om moeten gaan om iedereen te kunnen blijven voeden. Zeewier zal daarbij een belangrijke rol spelen. Wil je kennis maken met een van de vele zeewierproducten doe dan mee met onze win-actie. Win een super gave Reclaim-the-sea hoody en 3 multi-boxen (21x15g) Seamanchips. Wat moet je doen:1. Volg ons en @seaflavours.nl 2. Tag 3 vrienden die deze chips zeker moeten gaan proeven. Deze actie loopt tot en met 26 oktober 2019.
